Mention was made above (Chapter V, note) of this passage in the Life of Antonius. Though Ennodius speaks of ‘ the Pannonias,' the connection makes it clear that his account is intended to apply also to Noricum, particularly the territory about Lauriacum. Antonius was nephew os Constantius, bishop of Lauriacum, who is named below (Chapter XXX), and after the death of Severinus remained at Lau- riacum under the protection of his uncle until the latter’s decease.
